This paper deals with the study of bargaining networks, which is a topic in game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). The paper also discusses the computational tractability of finding solutions in bargaining networks, which suggests that it could belong to categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of local dynamics and market agents, which could indicate a connection to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
